title: VIDEO: Section 7AAA Championship Stage Set
text:
VIDEO: Section 7AAA Championship Stage Set 
By Norman Seawright III October 17, 2015 Updated Oct 17, 2015 at 10:46 PM CDT 
(NNCNOW.com) -- The Section 7AAA Minnesota State High School League (MSHSL) football playoffs continued, with two powerhouse schools heading for a championship collision. 
No. 2 Esko defeated No. 3 Two Harbors, despite an Agate offense that reliably scored in the first two quarters, by a score of 41-14. 
Facing the Eskomos is No. 1 Proctor, who defeated No. 4 Greenway/Nashwauk-Keewatin 40-6 after holding the Titans scoreless for three quarters. 
The Eskomos and the Rails will play at Malosky Stadium on October 22.
